# Full specs, then push (Sync2Dine)

## Never half-ship

- Do **not** mark a plan item done when only schema, stubs, or inject-without-admin exist.
- For knowledge / brains / Sales Brain: Supabase **read+write**, API, UI (if specified), and live verification are required before “done”.
- Do not advertise LIVE / ready / canSend when the underlying client or cloud store cannot perform the action.

## Push order (after debug)

1. Fix and verify on **https://app.sync2dine.io** (and Supabase cloud rows where relevant).
2. Then push **all three**: GitHub `origin/master` (frontend + backend as needed) ? Supabase migrations if any ? VPS API sync/restart + SPA deploy when UI changed.
3. Do **not** push “for later” incomplete slices as if they completed the plan.

